  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - NECROMANCER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>FIGHTING TECHNIQUES.</font> - <small>Kaeldair, Povar</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>First of all, this covers nearly EVERY aspect of hunting, killing, etc.  For all those who cannot handle reading a post for long, LEAVE NOW.  That said, let's begin.<br><br>

You've just hit level 8, you at least have these spells, if you don't...GET THEM!<br>
<br>
Bone Walk<br>
Dark Pact<br>
Lesser Shielding<br>
Ward Undead<br>
<br>
These are the essentials, try to get all of them...but if not, oh well.<br>
<br>
At level 8, you don't get any new DoT's, or a new Life-Drain series, so this is a pretty tough level.  The new pet is nice, but helps little.  Chances are you still have a weapon...I did not.  These were my memorized spells in order.<br>
<br>
Clinging Darkness<br>
Lifespike<br>
Dark Pact<br>
Poison Bolt<br>
Disease Cloud<br>
Siphon Strength<br>
Shadowstep<br>
Gate<br>
<br>
The reason for memorizing both Shadowstep AND Gate is this.  Shadowstep will get you a ways away from the MoB, hopefully enough to cast gate <br>
<br>
Some people think to memorize their pet and shielding spell all of the time, THIS IS NOT NECESSARY.  Only memorize those when you need to recast them, it won't kill you.<br>
<br>
That is correct, Fear is not up there, and for good reason, Fear is a mana/time hog, and normally doesn't work.  Don't use it at this level.<br>
<br>
Depending on what your hunting, you might want to tank for your pet, it does not matter, but do not hunt anything with poison.  If you do, most likely you AND your pet will get poisoned, increasing downtime threefold.<br>
<br>
Some might complain that Magicians do it, and there is a simple answer, the Magician water pet is immune to poison. <br>
<br>
Do not Shadowstep in areas like Oasis, it might be good that you got away from that croc, but landing face to face with a Spectre or a Deepwater Goblin might spoil your day.  (By the way, Deepwater Goblins are the coolest creatures on Norrath <br>
<br>
If you are hunting undead, always practice Evocation before hand and use Ward Undead.  <br>
<br>
Whatever you do, get to 12!<br>
<br>
Alright at 12, great level. New spells, better than 8.  Get these at all costs!<br>
<br>
Bind Affinity<br>
Leach<br>
Lifedraw<br>
Heat Blood<br>
Convoke Shadow<br>
<br>
On another note, Engulfing Darkness is the upgrade to Clinging Darkness, and has a higher resist rate than the lesser spell.  I did not use it.<br>
<br>
Sight Graft is pretty much useless, I did not buy it.<br>
<br>
This time I will give you a step by step account of my personal gameplay during these level's which are much more fun than 8-12.<br>
<br>
Many will suggest Oasis, but in my opinion it is dangerous (Spectres, Hill Giants, Ghouls, Dry Bones Skeletons) and it is very crowded.  If you do go there, try to find a group, and keep Gate handy, DO NOT BIND IN OASIS.<br>
<br>
I went to Sister Island.  The most important thing about this is NOT TO BIND ON THE ISLAND, you will never get out short of being teleported.  Also, if you plan on keeping faction, do not go here.  If you are already KoS, enjoy <br>
<br>
Bind on the docks and be sure to jump off the boat.<br>
<br>
This is an ACTUAL BATTLE ACCOUNT!<br>
<br>
<em>You begin casting Clinging Darkness.<br>
Sister of Erollisi is enfulfed in Darness.</em><br>
(Running break here, in the direction of waiting pet)<br>
<em>You begin casting Heat Blood.<br>
Sister of Erollisi's blood simmers.<br>
Sister of Erollisi slashes YOU for 17 points of damage!</em><br>
(Another running break, by this time 1/4 of her health is gone)
<em>/pet kill</em><br>
(I won't go into the details of the tanking)<br>
<em>You begin casting Leach<br>
Sister of Erollisi pales.</em><br>
(Meditate break here)
<em>/pet report health<br>
I have 38 percent of my health remaining.<br>
You begin casting Lifedraw.<br>
"Ahhh, I feel much better now"<br>
Sister of Erollisi staggers.<br>
You stagger.<br>
You beam a smile at Sister of Erollisi.<br>
Sister of Erollisi died.<br>
<b>You gain experience!</b></em><br>
<br>
I finished this fight and most others with FULL HEALTH and about 2-3 bubbles of mana.  Of course, those were IDEAL FIGHTS!  If 2 come, or one resists any spells, things become complicated, but nothing you can't handle, right?<br>
<br>
Sisters will take you merrily to 15, at which point you are on your own, because it is dark, and I am weary, fare all ye well fellow practitioners of the dark arts!<br></p>	</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
